  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life Skills training for VI with Enable India, Ban</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims towards personal development and self- integration of the disabled into the mainstream. Its purpose is to create an atmosphere whereby all Visually Impaired (VI) individuals of employable age get opportunities to learn important life skills which will enable them to secure employment in open market resulting in their total inclusion with confidence. 

The Project conducts life skills education training with the VIs and also conducts Training of Trainers for creating a pool of master trainers who may further pass on the skills to the VIs in their work area. 

The project also provides intensive counselling to the trained candidates and conducts sensitization workshops with the potential employers in order to ensure smooth transition of the candidates in their work place. 

The objectives of the project are 
&#x2022; To integrate life skills training as an important part of the holistic development of a person with disability. 
&#x2022; To ensure that the trainers of the VI are equipped with necessary skills to handle their real lives issues and train them with adequate skills.</narrative>
  </description>
